OLS Estimation

Let’s estimate our regression model \(Y_t = \beta_0 + \beta_1{X_t} + \beta_2{Z_t} + u_t\), and plot what the series are revealing:

OLS

Durbin Watson Test for Autocorrelation

The estimation results of the following specification of the static model is as follows:

##  lag Autocorrelation D-W Statistic p-value
##    1        0.187961      1.477713    0.15
##  Alternative hypothesis: rho != 0

We observe positive DW value, it may have AC problem since we do not know the intervals of upper and lower d statistics. Prob[DW] = 0.15 > 0.05 do not Rho. NO AC problem.

## 
##  Durbin-Watson test
## 
## data:  model1
## DW = 1.4777, p-value = 0.06946
## alternative hypothesis: true autocorrelation is greater than 0

However, in other DW Test, our p value results 0.06.

Breusch-Pagan Test for Autocorrelation

The estimation results of the following specification of the static model is as follows:

## 
##  studentized Breusch-Pagan test
## 
## data:  model1
## BP = 0.22615, df = 2, p-value = 0.8931

Do not RHo, there is no HC at \(\alpha\) = 0.05 level of significance.

Task 2

OLS Estimation of dynamic model

Task 2 requires the estimation of dynamic model, \(Y_t = \alpha_0 + \alpha_1{Y_{t-1}} + \alpha_2{X_{t}} + \alpha_3{Z_{t}} + \alpha_4{X_{t-1}} + \alpha_5{Z_{t-1}} + \epsilon_t\) with ARDL(1,1,1).

## 
## Call:
## lm(formula = Y ~ X + Z + Ylag + Xlag + Zlag, data = data)
## 
## Residuals:
##      Min       1Q   Median       3Q      Max 
## -172.370   -6.908    8.162   20.312   64.664 
## 
## Coefficients:
##             Estimate Std. Error t value Pr(>|t|)
## (Intercept)  38.4490    40.9642   0.939    0.366
## X             1.9980     1.5231   1.312    0.214
## Z            -0.3356    67.4958  -0.005    0.996
## Ylag          0.2075     0.3450   0.601    0.559
## Xlag          0.8961     1.5813   0.567    0.581
## Zlag         64.2615   105.8238   0.607    0.555
## 
## Residual standard error: 60.01 on 12 degrees of freedom
##   (1 observation deleted due to missingness)
## Multiple R-squared:  0.8436, Adjusted R-squared:  0.7784 
## F-statistic: 12.94 on 5 and 12 DF,  p-value: 0.0001732

Therefore, our model becomes \(\widehat{Y_{t}} = 38.4489659 + 1.9979573 X_{t} + -0.335551 Z_{t} + 0.2074751 Y_{t-1} + 0.8961434 X_{t-1} + 64.2615012 Z_{t-1}\)
